{"article_id":"vWRCrHCoPvnfbjAf","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Affordable Care Act is in deep trouble","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"- in Washington and large swaths of the country .","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Senate Republicans began to coalesce around the framework of a plan","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"to repeal","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"and replace the law","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"last week .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Their plan would , like the bill","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"the House passed in May ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"almost certainly cause millions of low-income Americans to lose coverage","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"by ending the Medicaid expansion .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"It would help the young and healthy at the expense of the older and the sick .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"Meanwhile , across the nation , health insurance plans are beginning to flee the Obamacare marketplace .","depth":4},{"id":12,"text":"They ' ve cited the uncertainty around the health care law ' s future ,","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"sown by congressional Republicans and the Trump administration .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"The number of counties with zero health plans","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"signed up","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"to sell 2018 coverage","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"keeps growing .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"The possibility","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"that Republicans will repeal Obamacare","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"or drive it into collapse","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"is an increasingly real one .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"That ' s a reality","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"where millions fewer have health insurance","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"and lower-income Americans struggle to afford coverage .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"\" Slowly but surely ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"I think","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"we ' re gon na get there , \"","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Sen. John Cornyn","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"( R-TX ) ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"the No . 2 Republican , told reporters on Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"regarding Obamacare repeal .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"\" We ' re coming together . \"","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"The Senate repeal plan is coming together","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"- and looks a lot like the House repeal plan","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Behind closed doors , Senate Republicans have worked out a path toward Obamacare repeal .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"The plans under discussion would end Medicaid expansion ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"causing millions of low-income Americans to lose health coverage .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"They may allow health insurance plans to charge higher premiums to people with preexisting conditions , too .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"In other words :","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"The emerging bill looks a whole lot like the unpopular bill","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"the House passed last month .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"It creates the same group of winners","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"( high-income , healthier people )","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"and the same group of losers","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"( low-income , sicker people ) .","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"The Republican plan is coming together","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"because moderate senators are beginning to drop some of their initial repeal objections .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Sens . Rob Portman","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"( R-OH )","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"and Shelley Moore Capito","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"( R-WV ) ,","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"for example , now back a plan","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"to end the Medicaid expansion .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"Both were ardent critics of the House bill ' s deep Medicaid cuts ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"which would cause 14 million Americans","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"who rely on the public program","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"to lose coverage .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Portman put out a harsh statement the day","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"the House passed its health care bill .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"\" I ' ve already made clear","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"that I don ' t support the House bill","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"as currently constructed","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"because I continue to have concerns","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"that this bill does not do enough","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"to protect Ohio 's Medicaid expansion population , \"","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"Portman said plainly .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"But now Portman has endorsed a plan","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"to phase out the Medicaid expansion entirely ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"just to do so on a longer timeline than the House bill .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Portman and Moore Capito want a seven-year phase out , rather than the House bill ' s three-year off-ramp .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"At the end of the day , though , phasing out Medicaid expansion over seven years has the same effect as three years :","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"You end coverage for millions of low-income Americans .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"There are still major issues","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"that divide Senate Republicans on repeal .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"There is disagreement , for example , over how much to cut the Medicaid program and what kind of subsidies to give people in the private market .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"But the fact","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that Republicans are coalescing around ending Medicaid expansion","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"- once thought to be a major sticking point -","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"suggests","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"the path to repeal may be easier to find than initial expectations .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"Insurance plans are scaling back their Obamacare participation","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"or quitting the marketplace entirely .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Most cite the growing uncertainty over the law ' s future","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"whether it will be repealed","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"and how the Trump administration will implement it .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"In the past week , the number of counties with zero health plans","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"signed up","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"to sell Obamacare","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"has doubled .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"There are now 38,000 Obamacare enrollees scattered across 47 counties","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"where no insurers want to participate in the marketplaces .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"In these places , Obamacare 's coverage expansion could vanish","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"regardless of whether Congress passes a repeal bill .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"People with Obamacare subsidies would still technically get that help ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"but would have no place","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"to actually buy coverage .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"Anthem announced last week","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"that it would exit the Ohio marketplace ,","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"leaving 20 counties and 15,000 Obamacare enrollees with no 2018 option .","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"Anthem has been lukewarm on the 2018 marketplaces .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"Reports earlier this spring from analysts","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"who follow the company","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"it was \" leaning towards exiting. \"","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"But Anthem has decided to stick with a few marketplaces .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"An Anthem exit in the rest of the states","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"where it currently sells","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"would be devastating to the law ,","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"leaving 300,000 Obamacare enrollees without coverage .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"When Blue Cross Blue Shield Kansas City quit on May 24 ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"it blamed the \" uncertain direction of this market . \"","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"The Affordable Care Act relies in large part on private health plans","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"volunteering to sell coverage on these public marketplaces .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"There are not mechanisms in the law","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"to force insurers to participate .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"\" We elected to have a system","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"that is completely market-based","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"so companies get to make individual decisions , \"","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"says Andy Slavitt ,","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"who served as Medicare administrator in the Obama administration .","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"Under the Trump administration , it has become increasingly difficult for health plans to make the decision","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"to participate on a marketplace","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"the president says","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"is \" exploding. \"","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"Who wants to build a business around a law","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"that the White House is actively trying to tear down ?","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"\" The information","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"we ' ve seen","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"coming from the administration","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"actually creates more uncertainty","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"rather than creating greater certainty , \"","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"says Brad Wilson , chief executive of Blue Cross Blue Shield North Carolina .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"Whenever a health insurance plan quits Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"I usually receive an email from the Health and Human Services press office","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"arguing","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"that this is all the more reason","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"Congress needs to repeal Obamacare .","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"This is the statement","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"that spokesperson Alleigh Marré sent out","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"when Anthem quit the Ohio marketplace last Tuesday","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"( bolding my own ) :","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"This news is heartbreaking for the millions of Ohioans","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"who depend on access to affordable , high-quality healthcare ,","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"and this is a stark reminder","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"that Obamacare is collapsing .","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"Now is the time","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"to advance real healthcare reform","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"that empowers individuals and families with the choices and resources","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"they need","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"to buy a plan","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"that meets their healthcare needs","depth":15},{"id":154,"text":"without breaking their budgets .","depth":15},{"id":155,"text":"The American people can ' t afford to wait any longer .","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"When Republican legislators talk","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"about why they need to repeal Obamacare ,","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"they point to the areas","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"that are struggling to attract health insurers .","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"They point to Obamacare 's bald spots","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"and make the argument","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"that a new law is needed","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"to fix the problem .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"`` What kind of protection is Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"if there are no plans","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"to choose from ? ''","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"House Speaker Paul Ryan said at the Rose Garden ceremony last month","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"to celebrate the House bill ' s passage .","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"When insurance executives talk","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"about why they 're leaving ,","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"they point the finger back at the uncertainty","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"Republicans are sowing .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"They don ' t want a new law ;","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"they want more certainty around existing law .","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"Specifically , they want to know","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"whether the administration will pay for a key subsidy program","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"that it has so far waffled on implementing .","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"\" The discussion","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"that is happening in Washington ,","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"that creates additional uncertainty , \"","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"says Geoff Bartsh , a vice president at health plan Medica ,","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"which sells on the marketplaces .","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"\" When you ' re dangling the cost-sharing subsidies","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"- they ' re on the table ,","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"they ' re off the table -","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"that creates uncertainty . \"","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"Insurers ' exits from Obamacare do n't just mean fewer ( or no ) choices for the millions of Americans","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"who rely on the law .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"They also give Republicans more ammo","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"for pushing their repeal plan forward","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"- and make the path","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"toward passing a Senate bill","depth":12},{"id":193,"text":"an easier one","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"to forge .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":389,"left":196,"right":388,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":196,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":388,"left":211,"right":387,